events.name: Golden State Warriors at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry can already sense the momentum building inside the Golden State Warriors' locker room.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 29 of 42 points in 1st half, hits 11 3s to help Warriors beat Pacers, 131-109

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner scored 34 points and the Orlando Magic weathered a 30-point second half by San Antonio's Devin Vassell to beat the Spurs 127-111 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner leads Magic past Spurs, who get 30-point second half from Devin Vassell

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 27 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the short-handed Brooklyn Nets 118-95 on Thursday night for their eighth straight victory and 16th in 17 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers beat short-handed Nets 118-95 for 8th straight victory and 16th in 17 games

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 39 points, 11 assists and eight rebounds to lead the Dallas Mavericks to a 122-108 victory Thursday night over the New York Knicks, who had just seven players in the second half because of injuries and trades.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 39 points to lead Mavericks to 122-108 victory over short-handed Knicks

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 30 points, Andre Drummond added 21 points and 13 rebounds, and the Chicago Bulls rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 118-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan, Andre Drummond lead Bulls past Grizzlies 118-110

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards had 26 points and nine assists and the Minnesota Timberwolves shot 21 of 41 from 3-point range to trounce the slumping Milwaukee Bucks 129-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves roll past short-handed Bucks 129-105 to spoil Doc Rivers' home debut

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 31 points, Bradley Beal had 30 and the Phoenix Suns — with All-Star Devin Booker sidelined by a sore left hip — beat the Utah Jazz 129-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 31 points, Bradley Beal adds 30 in Suns' 129-115 victory over Jazz

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 29 points, Michael Porter Jr. added 27 and the Denver Nuggets snapped the Los Angeles Lakers' three-game winning streak with a 114-106 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jamal Murray scores 29 points and Nuggets hold off Lakers in the final minutes for a 114-106 victory

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jalen Duren had 27 points and 21 rebounds and the Detroit Pistons won consecutive games for the first time since October, overcoming Jerami Grant’s career-high 49 points to beat Portland 128-122 in overtime Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons win consecutive games for first time since October, beating Trail Blazers 128-122 in OT
